review_blob: Pours a copper-orange with a thick cream head.  Aroma is sweet yeast, light grain scent.  Flavor is sweet, full-mouth malt, slight alcohol at end (but doesnt taste like 12% abv).  great beer

Pours black with a thick coffee head.  aroma is rich malt and slightly sweet.  Low carbonation and a rich body.  Smooth maltiness with a light sweetness.  Feels light on the stomach despite the good flavor.  Nice stout.
Gold and slightly orange with a thick white head.  Aroma is sweet, wheat and a slight fruit note.  Has a nice solid body and the flavor is wheat, not too sweet, with a little bite of spice.  Good Hef
Deep red brown with a thick brown head.  Aroma is malt and smooth.  Light bodied with light flavor as well, malty, and very drinkable.  No hint of the high abv in the flavor.  Very drinkable brew.

Pours dark red-orange-brown with a thin cream head.  Aroma is malt, hops, tich and deep with a light sweetness.  The tastes is somewhat subdued, slightly richer than the regular arrogant bastard.  The balance seems maltier with slightly less hop bitterness, though still tons of hops.  Bonus--> comes in a 6 pack

Pours a dark red brown with a thin cream head.  Aroma s sweet, grapefruit, citrus, and hops.  Flavor is light bodied with grapefruit acidity, mild hop bitterness that sharpens at the end,  High carbonation.

Pours black with a decent cream head that leaves terrific thick tracing along the pitcher/glass.  Aroma is faint of roast malt.  Flavor is smooth, rich, light chocolate on the back end with alcohol warmth but not taste.  Overall gets a 16 for being right down the street.

Early 2008 release -- Pours an orange red with a yellow/tan head.  Aroma is sweet and thick.  rich with malt and grain scents.  Flavor is strong malt with hops balancing it at the back end.  smooth with that slight hop bitterness, but surprisingly no alocohol taste given the high abv.  Good beer

Pours a dark brown with a coffee colored head.  Aroma is rich coffee, malt, light hops and very light alcohol.  Flavor is rich, though not too heavy.  lively carbonation with heavy coffee and malt notes with a taste of dark chocolate at the back of the throat.

Pours an orange-peach iced tea with a head thats gone before you blink.  Not much to smell at all, just very light notes of cranberry.  The taste is surprisingly spicy, like a cranberry cider.  Its interesting but I have a hard time getting any beer flavor out of it.  Highly carbonated and it leaves an unusual aftertaste (reminiscent of cough syrup).

Pours a deep red brown with a thin cream head.  Smells sweet with light fruit and hops.  Flavor is smooth with lively carbonation.  Satisfying hops with a sweet (but not malty) note.  Much better out of the glass than out of the bottle (duh)

Pours a dark brown (just a hint of red when held to the light) with a thick brown head.  Aroma is faint of malty richness.  Beer is heavy and smooth, low carbonation and malty but relatively unbalanced, light on flavor ... with a light chocolate flavor at the end.
UPDATED: FEB 4, 2008
Deep red brown with a decent cream brown head.  Aroma is sweet malt, fruit, and butter.  Flavor is terific, rich, smooth with sweet flavor coating the sides of the tongue.
pale yellow with a thick white head... little aroma... little flavor (mostly water)... easy to drink but no great beer
red brown with a thin head.  malt aroma with light caramel notes.  Beer is smooth but lively carbonated with medium flavor.

Pours deep red-brown with a decent head.  Aroma is light with fruit scents.  Taste is initially wheaty (like a hefeweizen) with rich malt tones and slight fruit to finish.  Very good beer, and at a terrific price.
Pours ruby brown with a thick lasting cream head that leaves traces on the glass.  Aroma is malt, coffee, and slight caramel.  Taste is malt and coffee, with a rich thick body.  Very nice.

Pours a deep red-brown with a thick lasting cream head.  Aroma is sweet, and malty with a strong peach scent.  It tastes sweet and slightly fruity which gives way to a grapefruit citrus bitterness from the hops at the finish.  Delicious.

Pours a transparent blonde with a thick but quickly dissipating white head.  Aroma is light and primarily hops.  The flavor matches the aroma, light hops but without excessive bitterness.  Relatively unremarkable overall, but decent for a pilsener.
UPDATED: DEC 26, 2007
Pours black.  With a thick brown head.  Aroma is malty with coffee and caramel notes.  Tastes roasted with strong coffee flavor and a little hop bite at the end.

Pours an amber (duh) with a fairly thick white head.  Aroma is very light and smells just enough of hops that you know your smelling a beer.  Flavor is light malt and hops with nothing spectacular about it.

Pours orange-peach with a thickcream head.  Aroma is roast malt and slightly smoky.  Flavor is a little light, especially for what I expected from a scottish ale called "kiltlifter".  Mildly malty and smoky with a light hoppiness.
beer_name: Four Peaks Kilt Lifter Scottish Style Ale

review_blob: Pours an orange peach with a nice cream head.  Aroma is hops, malt, and apple.  Flavor is malty smooth with a hoppy bitterness that grows at the finish.  Subtle and understated sweetness that makes this a very drinkable brew.

22oz bottle -- pours a caramel brown, ruby when held to the light with a thick off-white head that lasts.  Aroma is hoppy with grapefruit notes.  Flavor is malty on the front of the tongue, and has great grapefruit hoppiness on the back.  Finishes relatively clean.  Surprisingly less sharp than the Stone IPA.
UPDATED: DEC 16, 2007

12oz bottle.  Pours a transparent red-brown with a thick, mostly lasting cream head.  Aroma is slightly sweet and toasty.  The taste is also mildly sweet with notes of roasted malt and and a little hop bitterness at the end.

12oz bottle -- pours a deep ruby brown with a dissipating brown head that leaves traces on the glass.  Aroma is rich of roasted malt and honey.  Flavor is malty and smooth, though less strong than I expect from a porter.  Very drinkable though.
Bottle from variety pack.  Pours a deep brown with a thin light brown quickly dissipating head.  Aroma is malt and slightly sweet.  Tastes smooth and malty, softer than you expect from a dark beer.

22oz bottle.  golden orange with a decent cream head that dissipates leaving traces on the glass.  Aroma is very hoppy with a hint of wood.  Taste is full of hops with a grapefruit bitterness.  Finishes dry with no excessively bitte aftertaste, just a hint of that grapefruit..

750ml bottle.  Surprisingly delicious for a fruit flavored beer.  Pours a cloudy golden blonde with a white quickly dissipating head.  The aroma is of apples and wheat.  The apple flavor is suprisingly subtle when tasted though.  A delicious balance of sweet wheat notes that call to mind a hefeweizen with a hint of apple. A fine beer for dessert or with a snack.

500ml bottle -- Pours an intriguing orange-amber with a thin white quickly dissapating head.  Aroma is of yeast with a slight sweetness.  It is very fizzy with an initially thin feel in the mouth that eventually coats the back of the tongue.  The flavor is lightly sweet but overwhelmed by a strong bitterness

750ml bottle.  Pours a deep amber brown with a thick cream colored head.  Aroma is of fruit (plum?) and slight alcohol.  The body is full with soft carbonation and a medium/thick texture.  It tastes of fruit, malt, and alcohol with bitterness at the end.
